result.execSummary:
The defendant Louis D Walker was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Louis D Walker is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Louis D Walker was found guilty of Homicide by Intoxicated Use of Vehicle, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.09(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

8:27 Defendant Louis D Walker in court with attorney Eric Sheets.  Defendant Louis D Walker in custody.  Craig Lambert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Alicia Brundidge is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Lambert. She is a deputy with the Wood County Sheriff's Department. On 5/17/14 she was dispatched to the scene of a traffic accident in the Town of Saratoga, Wood County. She observed a vehicle at the scene and a motorcycle on its side with a person lying face down on the ground. She spoke with defendant who stated he was the driver of the vehicle. Witnesses observed victim being ejected from his motorcycle. The defendant stated to her that he was stopped at the stop sign on County Road Z and turned left onto Highway 73 and did not see the motorcycle. The defendant consented to a blood draw, which was done at Riverview Hospital. It was mailed to the State Crime Lab. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. The victim was declared dead at the scene of the accident. Attorney Sheets cross-examines witness. Attorney Lambert redirects. 
Exhibits #1 & 2 are marked and received.
Attorney Lambert makes statement.
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Bound over for further proceedings. Bond is continued.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 12, 2014 at 09:00 am.
